						<summary>

						<p>This records an agreement given by the <hi rend="italic">‘Padineṇvishayattār’</hi> (corporation) of four townships, undertaking to contribute half a <hi rend="italic">paṇam</hi> on every hundred pearls sold at Kīḻaikkarai for meeting the requirements of worship and repairs in the temple of Niṉaittadu-muḍitta-Piḷḷaiyār at Aṉuttogaimaṅgalam in Śembi-nāḍu.</p>						

